# Trivy ignore file for the kube-coder devlaptop image scan (CI security-scan job).
#
# Only FALSE POSITIVES belong here. Genuinely no-fix findings are dropped by
# `ignore-unfixed: true` in .github/workflows/ci.yml; actionable findings are
# tracked as GitHub issues and must NOT be silenced here.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# code-server bundled-VS-Code version misparse (issue #71)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Trivy reads the bundled VS Code version (1.123.0) from
#   usr/lib/code-server/lib/vscode/package.json
# and matches it against *code-server* advisories. We pin code-server 4.123.0
# (devlaptop/Dockerfile), which is newer than every fix below (3.12.0 / 4.10.1
# / 4.99.4) — so these are false positives. The bundled npm/shell-quote copies
# live inside upstream code-server's VS Code and are not independently
# patchable; they are resolved by bumping the pinned code-server version, at
# which point Trivy re-evaluates them.
CVE-2021-3810
CVE-2023-26114
CVE-2025-47269
CVE-2019-16775
CVE-2019-16776
CVE-2019-16777
CVE-2018-7408
CVE-2026-9277
